<subSubSection lastPageId="520" lastPageNumber="521" pageId="519" pageNumber="520" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="519" pageNumber="520">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="520" lastPageNumber="521" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">
This Holarctic species is found in the arctic regions from European Russia to the Melville Peninsula and Southampton Island in eastern Nunavut, Canada (Lindroth 1966: 528). Fossil remnants of this species, dated between about 16,700 and 
<pageBreakToken pageId="520" pageNumber="521" start="start">18,100</pageBreakToken>
years B.P., have been unearthed in southeastern Iowa (Baker et al. 1986: 96); others from a Plio-Pleistocene sequence have been found in northwestern Greenland (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Böcher">Boecher</normalizedToken>
1995: 28).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
